Wall Street tumbled to its worst pointloss ever and the worst percentage decline since the FirstWorld War as a frenzy of stock selling stunned even the mostbearish market participants. "Everyone is in awe and the word'crash' is on everyone's mind," one trader said.    The Dow Jones industrial average fell 508 points to 1738, alevel it has not been at since the Autumn of 1986.    Volume soared to 603 mln shares, almost doubling theprevious record of 338 mln traded just last Friday. Reuter&#3;